## Backend (Express / Fastify)

- Route files in src/routes/ — one file per resource, mounts only path + method
- Controllers in src/controllers/ — handle request/response only, no business logic
- Services in src/services/ — all business logic and data access
- All async route handlers must be wrapped with asyncHandler utility
- Zod for all request validation (body, params, query) — never manual checks
- Environment variables: read process.env once in src/config/index.ts, use config object everywhere else
- HTTP status codes: always use named constants from http-status-codes (StatusCodes.OK, StatusCodes.NOT_FOUND, etc.)
- Error handling: throw HttpError instances from services, centralized error middleware handles all errors
- Structured logger (pino/winston) for all logging — never console.log()
- CORS: never wildcard (*) in production — explicit origin allowlist from config
- Auth: authenticate middleware applied to all protected routes before role/permission checks
- Role checks: requireRole() middleware — never inline role comparison in controller
- No :any TypeScript types — use Zod inferred types or explicit interfaces
- Graceful shutdown: handle SIGTERM/SIGINT, drain connections before exit
